# Standards

This page contains various security-related standards across government.

## Government Functional Standard GovS 007: Security

This functional standard is part of a [suite of functional standards](https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/functional-standards) designed to promote consistent and coherent working within government organisations and across organisational boundaries.

You can find the [GovS 007 on GOV.UK](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/government-functional-standard-govs-007-security).

## Minimum Cyber Security Standard

This is a 2018 minimum set of cyber security standards that government expects departments to adhere to and exceed wherever possible.

You can find the [Minimum Cyber Security Standard on GOV.UK](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-minimum-cyber-security-standard).
